President Obama has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key administration posts. These include Danny Glaser for Assistant Secretary for Terrorist Financing at the Department of the Treasury, Jon Leibowitz for Commissioner and Chairman of the Federal Trade Commission, Robert E. Patterson for Ambassador to Turkmenistan at the Department of State, and Paul Piquado for Assistant Secretary for Import Administration at the Department of Commerce. Each nominee has an extensive background and experience in their respective fields. President Obama expressed confidence in their abilities and looks forward to working with them in the future.